Cell.Text: Anything that confirms that Thorald isn't dead, but is being held captive. I know those Battle-Borns have it. | They'd be hiding it, of course. Wouldn't want it to get out that they've been lying this whole time. | But you might be able to butter them up enough to lower their guard.

Node.Caption: MS09AvulsteinStage20BranchTopic: What sort of proof do you need?

Cell.Text: [S] Last I'd heard, he'd been carted off to Northwatch Keep. Ever heard of it? | If you go in there, you don't come out. Ever. | Here, see for yourself. This is the last word I received. I'm telling you, he's gone for good.

Node.Caption: MS09ThoradQuestionFollowUp2: If Thorald is alive, where is he?

Cell.Text: I used some contacts in the Legion, asked some questions. Was told I should mind my own business.
What's there to say? You go against the Empire, you wind up dead. Thorald got what was coming to him. | Best not to ask too many questions about it. People might get the wrong idea about you.
I think you know what really happened to Thorald Gray-Mane. (Persuade)

[S] Between the two of us, his family is better off thinking he's dead. | Thorald and I have history, all right? We used to be friends. So I looked into it when he disappeared. | I found out the Thalmor have him. And they don't let anyone go. | So I've kept my mouth shut. Like I said, his family is better off believing he's gone, because he's never coming back.
I think you know what really happened to Thorald Gray-Mane. (Persuade)
He fought on the wrong side, and he paid for it. That's all I have to say.
Oh come on, leave it alone. He's gone. There's no use in talking about it anymore. | I wish everyone could just get past that and get on with their lives.
Is there anything you can tell me about Thorald?
It's been a while now. I miss him, but it's clear he's not coming back. | He knew what he was getting into. I don't... I don't blame anyone.

Node.Caption: MS09ThoraldQuestionsBranchTopic: What do you know about Thorald Gray-Mane?

Cell.Text: You what? | Oh no. No, no, no. This can't be happening. | Please, you can't tell anyone. It must remain a secret! I'll do whatever you want.

Node.Caption: MS09JonOlfinaBranchTopic: I found your letter to Olfina.

Cell.Text: What makes you think I know anything? Everyone knows he's dead and gone!

Node.Caption: MS09JonOlifnaFollowUp1: I want to know about Thorald Gray-Mane.

Cell.Text: [S] Okay, okay! | All I know is that Idolaf made some effort to find out what happened to him, but was told to stop asking questions. | He got some letter from the Legion and has left it alone since then. | I'll prove it to you, all right? I'll get you the letter. Just... meet me at the statue of Talos, and don't tell anyone about this.

Node.Caption: MS09JonOlfinaResponse1: Shall we see what your father thinks of this letter?

Cell.Text: He's my son. I just... I feel it in my heart. You'd understand if you had children.

Node.Caption: MS09Stage20FraliaBranch1Topic: How can you be sure Thorald is still alive?

Cell.Text: It's hardly a secret that they have ties to the Empire, and hate anyone who speaks out against it. | Thorald did worse. He took action against the Empire, and the Battle-Borns knew it.

The Battle-Borns. The Emperor's biggest boot-lickers here in Whiterun. | Their connections to the Empire and the Legion are well-known. When Thorald didn't return home, there was no question in my mind. | They knew Thorald supported the Stormcloaks, knew he was going to aid them in battle. Made sure he didn't come back. | Locked him up someplace to get back at my family. I'm sure of it.

Node.Caption: MS09Stage20FraliaBranch2Topic: Why do you think the Battle-Borns are involved?

Cell.Text: Haven't you heard it by now? | He made the mistake of supporting the Stormcloaks, and it cost him. Bitter news for his family, but a fate they should've expected.

Node.Caption: MS09Stage20IdolafThoraldInfoTopic: I need to know what happened to Thorald.

Cell.Text: [S] Here's the letter. Now leave me out of this.
